The paper discusses the impact of trends in advanced electronic systems' design on design verification technologies, which falls under the category of Embedded Systems (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the verification of hardware design models in multidimensional space, which involves aspects of computer architecture (cs.AR) and electromagnetics (cs.EM). The paper also mentions the need for verification of non-functional aspects such as power, reliability, and security, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
